<br>
That's like you running over a chicken, and the farmer sues you for the cost of the chicken, and all the chicken's probably decendants that he &quot;lost&quot; when you ran over the chicken.<br>
<br>
In that hour the greenies &quot;lose&quot; exp getting their corpse, they could just as easily have been wiped out by a train, blasted by an even-con evil, drowned, decided to go eat something, etc. That experience wasn't assured by any stretch of the imagination. FUrthermore, he had the same amount of exp after the event as he did before the event, and therefore LOST nothing whatsoever. A failure to gain an expected return is NOT the same thing as a loss. If you don't believe me, try to deduct a market loss from your taxes when your stocks don't do as well as they were projected to. The IRS will give you a definition of &quot;LOSS&quot; right quick.<br>
<br>
